Diference between const and let:
const declares a variable with a constant value.
 Meaning once you assign a value to a const variable, 
you cannot reasign it later in your code.

let declares a variable that can be reassigned later in your code.

- A string data type is a collection or sequence of characters treated 
as a single unit. 
lLStrings can include letters, numbers, symbols, and even spaces. 

Template literals are string literals that allow for embedded expressions.
 They are enclosed by the backtick (`) character instead of single or
  double quotes. Template literals can contain placeholders, which are 
  indicated by the dollar sign and curly braces (${expression}).

let name = 'Alicia';
let age = 25;
let message2 = `My name is ${name} and I am ${age} years old.`;

- index.html it's a common convention in web development to name the main
 entry point of a website or directory.
This convention originated from early web servers, which would automatically serve an "index.html" file when a directory was accessed without specifying a file name. 